   <title type="text">Ancient Language Spelling Correction</title>
   <content type="html"><![CDATA[I have recently become aware of two Latin spelling correction utilities:<br /><ul><li style="font-family: inherit;"><span style="font-size: small;"><a href="http://drouizig.org/index.php?option=com_content&amp;view=article&amp;id=75&amp;Itemid=68&amp;lang=en">COL - Correcteur Orthographique de Latin - Correttore Ortografico di Latino - Corrector Ortográfico de Latín</a></span></li><li><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: small;"><a href="http://extensions.services.openoffice.org/en/node/4293" title="Latin spelling and hyphenation dictionaries 2010.08.23">Latin spelling and hyphenation dictionaries</a> (for Open Office) </span><span style="font-family: inherit; font-size: small;">[n.b. this may require you to reload, but it will eventually appear]</span></li></ul>This makes me wonder if there are utilities like these for other ancient languages.&nbsp; If you have information, please respond in the comments.]]></content>
